    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-04-09T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-04-09T17:00:00-05:00" n="523"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d523">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.796/300: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-09T19:00:00-03:00"
                            >April 9, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>291. For the Under Secretary. Your 178 of April 7, 8 p.m. Aranha says that he has
                    no idea of making difficulties for our oil companies on this but that he is
                    extremely reluctant to do anything to interrupt the Lati service: it is he says
                    the only effective means aside from cable that he has of communicating with many
                    of his representatives in Europe and North and West Africa.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
